	     Harare - Zimbabwe's President Robert Mugabe on Monday demoted one of the top candidates to succeed him of a cabinet post, as the battle to replace the long-ruling leader intensifies. Vice President Emmerson Mnangagwa, who also doubled as minister of justice, was replaced by ruling Zanu-PF party loyalist Happyton Bonyongwe. Mnangagwa is now Minister of Tourism, NewZimbabe.com reported. Mnangagwa will stay on as one of the two Mugabe vice presidents.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  